  <compounddef id="EXP" kind="page">
    <compoundname>EXP</compoundname>
    <title>EXP Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">EXP(real-expression)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Returns <bold>e</bold> (Euler’s number, approximately <computeroutput>2.71828</computeroutput>) raised to the power of the given expression. In other words, <computeroutput>EXP(x)</computeroutput> = <computeroutput>e^x</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="EXP_1autotoc_md492">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>EXP(1)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces approximately <computeroutput>2.71828</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>EXP(0)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>1</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>EXP(2)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces approximately <computeroutput>7.38906</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Demonstrate<sp/>inverse<sp/>with<sp/>LOG</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">x#<sp/>=<sp/>5</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;x<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;;<sp/>x#;<sp/>&quot;<sp/><sp/>log(exp(x))<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;;<sp/>LOG(EXP(x#))</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="EXP_1autotoc_md494">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Argument may be any real number (positive, negative, or zero).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Return value is always positive.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>For natural logarithm (inverse of EXP), use <ref refid="LOG" kindref="compound">LOG</ref>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
